  "summary": "klaudius posts data to api.telegram.org via hardcoded bot endpoint",
  "details": "The package contains hardcoded outbound HTTP POST calls to https://api.telegram.org (Telegram Bot API) inside dist/bin.js and dist/chunk-SZ4KCTSL.js. The Telegram Bot API endpoint is a well-documented C2/exfiltration channel pattern: a hardcoded bot token in the URL path lets the publisher receive arbitrary data from any installer that runs the package, while the destination (api.telegram.org) is allowed by most egress filters. Combined with bundled/minified delivery in dist/, this matches the hardcoded-C2-exfiltration fingerprint. Installers running the CLI (dist/bin.js) will transmit data to an attacker-controlled Telegram bot.",
